{"data": {"repository": {"pullRequest": {"id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NTQzNzk2ODEy", "number": 4059, "reviewThreads": {"totalCount": 3, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0xMi0yMlQxNDozMzo0N1rOFILcwQ==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMS0wMS0wNVQxOToxODoxNVrOFLaDcA==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDIzOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3VGhyZWFkMzQ0MTIwNTEzOnYy", "diffSide": "RIGHT", "path": "docs/examples/wpi-many/wpi-many-custom-checker-example.sh", "isResolved": false, "comments": {"totalCount": 3, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0xMi0yMlQxNDozMzo0N1rOIJ9M4A==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0xMi0zMFQwMjoxMzo0NFrOIMb_og==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU0NzMxMDgxNg==", "bodyText": "Rather than modifying the last command, I think this script would be easier to use if there is logic that checks whether the variable is set and provides the --stubs option only if the variable is set.  Similarly for --libs.", "url": "https://github.com/typetools/checker-framework/pull/4059#discussion_r547310816", "createdAt": "2020-12-22T14:33:47Z", "author": {"login": "mernst"}, "path": "docs/examples/wpi-many/wpi-many-custom-checker-example.sh", "diffHunk": "@@ -24,7 +24,9 @@ checkername=no-literal\n repolist=securerandom.list\n workingdir=$(pwd)\n \n-# the stub files for the checker being used\n+# The stub files for the checker being used.\n+# If you are not using stub files, you MUST comment this line out and modify the last command in", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "9db300c4a374cd8d8d3e373cfbe2e3b06a3b7252"}, "originalPosition": 6}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU0OTQ3NDg1Ng==", "bodyText": "I don't disagree that the change you're suggesting would make the script easier to use. However, this script isn't meant to be used - it is an example/template for a user to write their own script. For that reason, the script's logic should be as simple as possible - the \"user\" is expected to read and understand the entire script, modifying each line for their use-case as they go. No one should run this script without first understanding it and modifying it themselves.", "url": "https://github.com/typetools/checker-framework/pull/4059#discussion_r549474856", "createdAt": "2020-12-28T20:17:31Z", "author": {"login": "kelloggm"}, "path": "docs/examples/wpi-many/wpi-many-custom-checker-example.sh", "diffHunk": "@@ -24,7 +24,9 @@ checkername=no-literal\n repolist=securerandom.list\n workingdir=$(pwd)\n \n-# the stub files for the checker being used\n+# The stub files for the checker being used.\n+# If you are not using stub files, you MUST comment this line out and modify the last command in", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU0NzMxMDgxNg=="}, "originalCommit": {"oid": "9db300c4a374cd8d8d3e373cfbe2e3b06a3b7252"}, "originalPosition": 6}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU0OTkxMjQ4Mg==", "bodyText": "The fewer modifications are necessary, the fewer errors users are likely to make.  I think it is better to make the script just a little bit more capable, rather than leaving landmines for less-than-perfect users to stumble over.", "url": "https://github.com/typetools/checker-framework/pull/4059#discussion_r549912482", "createdAt": "2020-12-30T02:13:44Z", "author": {"login": "mernst"}, "path": "docs/examples/wpi-many/wpi-many-custom-checker-example.sh", "diffHunk": "@@ -24,7 +24,9 @@ checkername=no-literal\n repolist=securerandom.list\n workingdir=$(pwd)\n \n-# the stub files for the checker being used\n+# The stub files for the checker being used.\n+# If you are not using stub files, you MUST comment this line out and modify the last command in", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU0NzMxMDgxNg=="}, "originalCommit": {"oid": "9db300c4a374cd8d8d3e373cfbe2e3b06a3b7252"}, "originalPosition": 6}]}}, {"id": "MDIzOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3VGhyZWFkMzQ3MTc3MzE3OnYy", "diffSide": "RIGHT", "path": "docs/examples/wpi-many/wpi-many-custom-checker-example.sh", "isResolved": false, "comments": {"totalCount": 4, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMS0wMS0wNVQwMDowMDozN1rOIOFcqA==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMS0wMS0wNVQxNzozODoyOFrOIOgs5Q==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU1MTY0MDIzMg==", "bodyText": "I wouldn't think these variables should be quoted, because they represent multiple tokens.  If this works as is, then fine.", "url": "https://github.com/typetools/checker-framework/pull/4059#discussion_r551640232", "createdAt": "2021-01-05T00:00:37Z", "author": {"login": "mernst"}, "path": "docs/examples/wpi-many/wpi-many-custom-checker-example.sh", "diffHunk": "@@ -71,6 +96,6 @@ bash wpi-many.sh -o \"${workingdir}/${checkername}-${repolistbase}\" \\\n      -t ${timeout} \\\n      -- \\\n      --checker \"${checker}\" \\\n-     --quals \"${qual_classpath}\" \\\n-     --lib \"${checker_classpath}\" \\\n-     --stubs \"${custom_stubs}\"\n+     \"${quals_arg}\" \\", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "ec553090fd371416b0f651a81a1803b1de1bc741"}, "originalPosition": 110}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU1MTY0MzI3NQ==", "bodyText": "My understanding has always been that variables that might be empty or contain whitespace should be quoted. This version also passes shellcheck as-is, though I didn't actually run the script (I don't have the environment to do so anymore).", "url": "https://github.com/typetools/checker-framework/pull/4059#discussion_r551643275", "createdAt": "2021-01-05T00:11:27Z", "author": {"login": "kelloggm"}, "path": "docs/examples/wpi-many/wpi-many-custom-checker-example.sh", "diffHunk": "@@ -71,6 +96,6 @@ bash wpi-many.sh -o \"${workingdir}/${checkername}-${repolistbase}\" \\\n      -t ${timeout} \\\n      -- \\\n      --checker \"${checker}\" \\\n-     --quals \"${qual_classpath}\" \\\n-     --lib \"${checker_classpath}\" \\\n-     --stubs \"${custom_stubs}\"\n+     \"${quals_arg}\" \\", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU1MTY0MDIzMg=="}, "originalCommit": {"oid": "ec553090fd371416b0f651a81a1803b1de1bc741"}, "originalPosition": 110}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU1MTcwNzk1Mw==", "bodyText": "If the variable is empty, your goal is not to pass a single empty token to the program; rather, your goal is to pass no tokens to the program.\nShellcheck assumes you want to pass a single token; a warning suppression is necessary in cases like this.", "url": "https://github.com/typetools/checker-framework/pull/4059#discussion_r551707953", "createdAt": "2021-01-05T04:17:36Z", "author": {"login": "mernst"}, "path": "docs/examples/wpi-many/wpi-many-custom-checker-example.sh", "diffHunk": "@@ -71,6 +96,6 @@ bash wpi-many.sh -o \"${workingdir}/${checkername}-${repolistbase}\" \\\n      -t ${timeout} \\\n      -- \\\n      --checker \"${checker}\" \\\n-     --quals \"${qual_classpath}\" \\\n-     --lib \"${checker_classpath}\" \\\n-     --stubs \"${custom_stubs}\"\n+     \"${quals_arg}\" \\", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU1MTY0MDIzMg=="}, "originalCommit": {"oid": "ec553090fd371416b0f651a81a1803b1de1bc741"}, "originalPosition": 110}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU1MjA4Njc1Nw==", "bodyText": "Thanks for the explanation. I looked through https://github.com/koalaman/shellcheck/wiki/SC2086 and found an alternative that avoids the shellcheck warning but also has the behavior we're looking for, I think, using alternate expansion (the discussion of this approach is near the bottom of that page).", "url": "https://github.com/typetools/checker-framework/pull/4059#discussion_r552086757", "createdAt": "2021-01-05T17:38:28Z", "author": {"login": "kelloggm"}, "path": "docs/examples/wpi-many/wpi-many-custom-checker-example.sh", "diffHunk": "@@ -71,6 +96,6 @@ bash wpi-many.sh -o \"${workingdir}/${checkername}-${repolistbase}\" \\\n      -t ${timeout} \\\n      -- \\\n      --checker \"${checker}\" \\\n-     --quals \"${qual_classpath}\" \\\n-     --lib \"${checker_classpath}\" \\\n-     --stubs \"${custom_stubs}\"\n+     \"${quals_arg}\" \\", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU1MTY0MDIzMg=="}, "originalCommit": {"oid": "ec553090fd371416b0f651a81a1803b1de1bc741"}, "originalPosition": 110}]}}, {"id": "MDIzOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3VGhyZWFkMzQ3NTA1NTIwOnYy", "diffSide": "RIGHT", "path": "docs/examples/wpi-many/wpi-many-custom-checker-example.sh", "isResolved": true, "comments": {"totalCount": 2, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMS0wMS0wNVQxOToxODoxNVrOIOj98A==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMS0wMS0wNVQxOToyMjo0MlrOIOkGqw==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU1MjE0MDI3Mg==", "bodyText": "This quoting is too broad.  It should be\n${quals_arg:+--quals \"${qual_classpath}\"}\n\n(See the very last example at https://github.com/koalaman/shellcheck/wiki/SC2086.)", "url": "https://github.com/typetools/checker-framework/pull/4059#discussion_r552140272", "createdAt": "2021-01-05T19:18:15Z", "author": {"login": "mernst"}, "path": "docs/examples/wpi-many/wpi-many-custom-checker-example.sh", "diffHunk": "@@ -71,6 +94,6 @@ bash wpi-many.sh -o \"${workingdir}/${checkername}-${repolistbase}\" \\\n      -t ${timeout} \\\n      -- \\\n      --checker \"${checker}\" \\\n-     --quals \"${qual_classpath}\" \\\n-     --lib \"${checker_classpath}\" \\\n-     --stubs \"${custom_stubs}\"\n+     ${quals_arg:+\"--quals ${qual_classpath}\"} \\", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "f2cdf384fa791d175b89fa7e309f6474752f961f"}, "originalPosition": 108}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU1MjE0MjUwNw==", "bodyText": "Nice catch. I've fixed it.", "url": "https://github.com/typetools/checker-framework/pull/4059#discussion_r552142507", "createdAt": "2021-01-05T19:22:42Z", "author": {"login": "kelloggm"}, "path": "docs/examples/wpi-many/wpi-many-custom-checker-example.sh", "diffHunk": "@@ -71,6 +94,6 @@ bash wpi-many.sh -o \"${workingdir}/${checkername}-${repolistbase}\" \\\n      -t ${timeout} \\\n      -- \\\n      --checker \"${checker}\" \\\n-     --quals \"${qual_classpath}\" \\\n-     --lib \"${checker_classpath}\" \\\n-     --stubs \"${custom_stubs}\"\n+     ${quals_arg:+\"--quals ${qual_classpath}\"} \\", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU1MjE0MDI3Mg=="}, "originalCommit": {"oid": "f2cdf384fa791d175b89fa7e309f6474752f961f"}, "originalPosition": 108}]}}]}}}, "rateLimit": {"limit": 5000, "remaining": 1895, "cost": 1, "resetAt": "2021-11-12T12:57:47Z"}}}